
- *Exercise recovery and PEM duration integration* ([Chapter 2, PEM measurement section updated; Chapter 5, severity levels section updated; Chapter 14a, core mechanisms section updated with epigenetic/EV hypotheses; Chapter 14d, cross-disease section updated with Long COVID comparison; Chapter 14f, CPET-derived section updated; Chapter 25b, proposed studies section updated; Appendix H, 11 new annotated entries; references.bib, 19 new entries; hypothesis-registry.typ, 6 new entries]): Comprehensive integration of 20-paper literature review on 2-day CPET, PEM recovery duration, and exercise testing in ME/CFS. Updated PEM measurement section with largest 2-day CPET study (Keller2024CPET), ICF discrimination evidence, and 24h interval limitation. Added severity vs PEM recovery patterns analysis with severity-independent PEM mechanism speculation. Added CPET-2 deterioration as ME/CFS-specific signature hypothesis. Added Long COVID vs ME/CFS PEM divergence hypothesis (null result from Gattoni2025LongCOVIDCPET). Added novel mechanistic insights: prolonged epigenetic recovery hypothesis (Sharma2025EpigeneticPEM) and EV-mediated intercellular signaling speculation (Giloteaux2024EVExercise). Added comprehensive multi-timepoint PEM recovery duration study proposal to Ch25b. Updated hypothesis registry with 6 new entries (3 hypotheses, 2 speculations, 1 study). _Motivated by:_ @Keller2024CPET — largest 2-day CPET study confirming Day 2 deterioration; @vanCampen2020SeverityCPET — severity patterns in 2-day CPET; @Sharma2025EpigeneticPEM — 48h epigenetic changes post-exercise; @Giloteaux2024EVExercise — EV proteome changes with exercise; @Gattoni2025LongCOVIDCPET — Long COVID null result showing no CPET-2 impairment.

	- *Vascular inflammation in neuropsychiatric Long COVID integration* ([Chapter 14k, 3 new hypothesis environments, 2 new speculation environments, 4 new open-question environments; mathematical model with limitation environment; Appendix H, 1 new annotated entry; references.bib, 1 new entry; hypothesis-registry.typ, 4 new entries]): Integration of McAlpine et al. 2026 vascular biomarker study demonstrating endothelial dysfunction WITHOUT overt coagulopathy in Long COVID, with cognitive and psychiatric symptom correlations. Added novel hypotheses extending Long COVID findings to ME/CFS: endothelial adhesion-cognition correlation (0.40), AGP neuroprotective biomarker speculation (0.25), vascular biomarker temporal evolution model (0.35). Added treatment proposals: anti-adhesion therapy for cognitive symptoms, biomarker-guided ME/CFS subtype stratification. Added formal limitation environment to speculative mathematical model. Fixed citation keys to use correct bib entries. Corrected ADAMTS13 classification error (VWF-cleaving protease, not endothelial adhesion molecule). Updated hypothesis registry with 4 new entries. _Motivated by:_ @McAlpine2026 — vascular inflammation correlates with cognitive/psychiatric symptoms in Long COVID; endothelial dysfunction distinction from coagulopathy; cross-disease mechanistic parallels with ME/CFS.
